Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Fisherman's Bible
Author: WILSON
Vol / Page: 224
Edition:
Quote: SCHOOLSHARK Not unlike a larger version of the Gummy shark (who grows to about fourfeet) the Schoolshark gets up to about eight feet and inhabits our / coastal waters ... The flesh, like that of the gummies, is quite edible and regularly marketed, usually as Lemonfish. The Schoolshark is usually dark-grey-green above and white below. Known also as Tope and Sand shark they are the only fish who close their eyes when they sleep.
Notes:

